Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["7. Ideal physical implementation: planar rotor (Eq. 17)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d784f3ce-76a8-df47-91d6-1a7265bad430"],

Cell["\<\
With rotor-GKP logical states |s> = |theta = 2 Pi s/d>, the phase operator \
e^{i theta} acts as Zbar_d, so the rotor conditional displacement D(alpha \
e^{i theta}) equals CD_d(alpha) exactly (Eq. 17). Residual should be 0.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"74910aec-026d-da47-809c-ef9b93da63d0"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
GeneralizedCD`GCDSetFockSize[50];
Table[d -> GeneralizedCD`RotorCDIdentityResidual[d, 1.3 + 0.2 I], {d, {2, 3, \
4, 6}}]\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[30]:=",ExpressionUUID->"0afcc87a-13f4-c241-bd42-d430a47565f7"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"2", "\[Rule]", "0"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"3", "\[Rule]", "0"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"4", "\[Rule]", "0"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"6", "\[Rule]", "0"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9920812215018845`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[31]=",ExpressionUUID->"8a6389f7-1753-b243-9a4e-6351ff38d0d5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
The harmonic-oscillator cat-code (beam splitter, Eq. 19) and the spin / \
Tavis-Cummings (Eq. 22) implementations approximate CD_d with fidelity \
approaching 1 as the encoding size grows (Fig. 4); those are documented as \
extensions in docs/plain_english_proof.md.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fc4957f6-4f60-d84b-8766-e61628f85473"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["8. Full validation suite and key findings", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"8c6379eb-a66d-a947-bca6-7ff97a9ddf8a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
GeneralizedCD`GCDSetFockSize[70];
GeneralizedCD`RunValidationSuite[] // Dataset\
\>", "Input",
